<title>HUNGARY: Hungary Jan-May private sector wages up 6.2 pct.</title>
<headline>Hungary Jan-May private sector wages up 6.2 pct.</headline>
<dateline>BUDAPEST 1997-07-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Real wages in Hungary's private sector rose by 6.2 percent in January-May, compared to a rise of 5.9 percent in January-April, the Central Statisticial Office (KSH) said on Monday.</p>
<p>In January-May 1996 real wages fell 4.5 percent year-on-year.</p>
<p>In the first five months of 1997, average net monthly wage in the private sector rose to 37,100, up 25.9 percent over the same period of 1996.</p>
<p>This compares to a CPI increase of 18.6 percent over the same period.</p>
<p>KSH added that white-collar workers' wages rose 12.0 percent, while blue collar workers' wages rose 1.9 percent in real terms.</p>
